Beijing hails round-up of Uighur ‘terrorists’ | The Times
China claimed yesterday that it had smashed 32 terrorist cells and arrested hundreds of suspects after a weekend of burnings, gunfire and bombings in the far western Xinjiang region. The crackdown was part of an effort by the authorities to show they are in control of a region where ethnic violence is escalating and militant Islam appears to be playing an increasing role.
